Insurance companies face data sprawl with disparate systems and¬error-prone manual processes impeding a holistic view of the business and risk exposure. Gaining this insight is critical at a time when the regulatory environment demands businesses improve their risk models and practices.

Using actuarial statistical analysis and modelling based upon Microsoft solutions, insurance companies are able to better identify risks, price¬policies more effectively, understand their liabilities more accurately,¬and optimise their financial positions.

As the pace of global financial services accelerates and speed becomes essential to decision-making, traditional tools are simply too slow. Coupled with massive on-premises server farms being unsustainably expensive, there is a real need for higher computing throughput but with a compelling TCO.

Microsoft analytics solutions enable financial institutions to benefit from cloud computing by reducing capex and facilitating more complex data analysis. Typical scenarios include risk computation and modelling plus predictive analytics through machine learning of data analysis & patterns.

• Gain deeper insight into¬   segmentation, profitability¬   and sentiment

Faced with exponentially increasing volumes of data, it is challenging for financial institutions to translate that data into insight needed to improve customer profitability and retention. To do this effectively, you need deeper insight into the profitability of you customer portfolio and have the ability to visualise that data so it is actionable.

With Microsoft customer and product analytics solutions, you can capitalise on internal and external data to combine profitability, segmentation and customer preference, to gain a complete end-to-end view of the customer.

Microsoft Dynamics AX- and Nav-based billing systems offer cost-effective, flexible solutions for billing, which can be easily integrated to the Dynamics CRM system for improved customer service. They can also link seamlessly to other corporate ERP solutions (eg SAP) allowing flexibility for part of your customer base whilst still leveraging existing assets for customers where less flexibility is needed.
Combine integrated insights and analytics tools with Microsoft Dynamics CRM to create a detailed 360-degree view of the customer.

Service agents can accommodate communication on many channels but still ensure a single customer journey.  Sales and Marketing benefit from a more personal view of the customer, to provide maximim value offers and engage at the right times.

Deliver a complete suit of management, productivity and actionable insights technology in an integrated and easy to deploy solution.  Combining the power of the Office 365 cloud productivity suite, with Microsoft CRM and billing solutions, the processing and scalability of the cloud as well as insight, reporting and machine learning capabilities of Microsoft Azure and Power BI, it is easy to 'spin up' a complete business unit.

Microsoft billing and CRM solutions provide detailed visibility of their service and product usage, helping to improve promotions, products, and services provided to customers.  Combined with service status data, Microsoft Dynamics CRM empowers staff to deliver exceptional customer experiences.  It also drives improvements in time-consuming procedures related to billing for customers, reducing total cost of ownership.

Microsoft Dynamics CRM provides organisations with closed-loop visibility of work across sales, engineering and production, to provide personalised and relevant one-to-one customer care experiences.  Automated alerts and escalations ensure a response to customers within set timeframes, and real-time visibility of all customer contacts and outstanding work enable staff to proactively manage contact volumes and incoming work cases.
